\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Average number of GMRES iterations for RK methods using the Diagonal preconditioner compared to a plain implicit solver without preconditioning. Notably, for smaller step sizes ($h \le 0.01$), the diagonal preconditioner degrades the spectrum and increases iteration counts compared to the un-preconditioned system. Values of 150.00 indicate GMRES stalled at the maximum iteration limit.\relax }}{4}{table.caption.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:diagonal_vs_none}{{2}{4}{Average number of GMRES iterations for RK methods using the Diagonal preconditioner compared to a plain implicit solver without preconditioning. Notably, for smaller step sizes ($h \le 0.01$), the diagonal preconditioner degrades the spectrum and increases iteration counts compared to the un-preconditioned system. Values of 150.00 indicate GMRES stalled at the maximum iteration limit.\relax }{table.caption.2}{}}
